comments: Rozier (CHA) legally contests Morris' (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) and Plumlee (CHA) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Plumlee (CHA) is already in Rivers' (DEN) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Morris (DEN) is already in Plumlee's (CHA) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Jokic (DEN) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes two steps after his gather before he passes the ball.
Plumlee (CHA) is retreating alongside Jokic's (DEN) path and absorbs the contact during the drive.
Plumlee (CHA) brings his arm down and makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Washington (CHA) is already in Rivers' (DEN) path and he releases away from the contact as the defenders switch.
Bridges (CHA) does not bring both hands to the ball when he brings his dribble to a pause.
Morris (DEN) makes contact with the part of Ball's (CHA) hand that is on the ball as they attempt to secure the rebound.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Ball (CHA) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Denver.
Ball (CHA) cleanly deflects the ball away from Morris (DEN).  Any ensuing body contact after the deflection is considered incidental.
Ball (CHA) cleanly dislodges the ball from Jokic (DEN).
Washington (CHA) makes contact with the ball and with the part of Jokic's (DEN) hand that is on the ball.
Jokic (DEN) and Washington (CHA) briefly engage and disengage as they attempt to secure the loose ball.

Replay review of the foul called on Washington (CHA) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Washington extends his arm into Morris' (DEN) body and initiates contact that affects his driving shot attempt.
Bridges (CHA) is already in Morris' (DEN) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Barton (DEN) legally contests Rozier's (CHA) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Plumlee (CHA) is moving alongside Jokic's (DEN) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
As Jokic (DEN) crosses over, he brings his left arm towards Plumlee's (CHA) forearm and briefly grasps his arm before immediately correcting as he continues his drive to the basket.
Plumlee (CHA) legally contests Jokic's (DEN) driving shot attempt.
Gordon (DEN) and Washington (CHA) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Bridges (CHA) commits a take foul on Jokic (DEN).
Rivers (DEN) briefly grasps Plumlee's (CHA) arm and releases his arm as they attempt to secure the rebound.
A jump ball is correctly whistled to determine possession after the ball is knocked out of bounds simultaneously by Plumlee (CHA) and Rivers (DEN).
Plumlee (CHA) and Green (DEN) make incidental contact with one another as they attempt to tip the jump ball.
